BRIEFING: DEPT GATE: B2 / ARR GATE: A4 (GATE(S) ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE) PAX COUNTS: F 16 / Y 148 / NR 15 (PAX COUNTS ARE PRELIMINARY)
NEW VERSION REPLACES KSFO FOR ETOPS DUE TO NOT LEGAL. NEW ETOPS ALT NOW KSJC.
KSLC: VFR CONDITIONS PREVAIL THROUGH THE TAF PERIOD. POSSIBLE CHOP/TURB FROM DEPT DUE TO A JTST. PREVAILING WINDS TRANSITIONING NORTHWESTERLY AROUND ROUGHLY 14Z TUESDAY.
ENRTE: HIGH PRESSURE MAINTAINS ITS PRESENCE OVER CEPAC. AN AREA OF FCSTD TURB BTWN W140 TO W150 MAY HAVE CHOP/TURB IN THIS AREA TO FL340, OTHERWISE, VFR AND NO SIGNIFICANT WX OVER TRACKS.
HAWAIIAN ISLANDS: A COMBINATION OF EASTERLY WINDS AND SEA BREEZES WILL AFFECT EACH ISLAND ON SUNDAY WITH CLOUDS BUILDING OVER MOUNTAIN AND INTERIOR SECTIONS IN THE AFTERNOON HOURS.
THREAT SPACE WEATHER: DISRUPTION TO HF OPS POSS DUE TO SPACE WX LEVEL R3 FCSTD AT 25%
NOTAMS PLEASE REVIEW NOTAMS SECTION OF PACKET FOR MOST CURRENT INFORMATION
